<p>
Lorod

Photo: Chase Hall

<p>Lorod “Original design is intuitive. It’s possessing the ability to think independently and create instinctively. Looking inward to set the climate in lieu of adjusting for the weather.” —Lauren Rodriguez “For me, originality is rooted in making work that is personal—creating clothing that renegotiates personal histories as a way to find newness. Truly original design has evolved into an amalgam of different techniques, styles, and tropes that are reconsidered to provide a new perspective. By combining different design elements that are personal to our lived experiences, we’re hoping to develop an original visual language in American fashion.” —Michael Freels</p>


